562
00:46:25,516 --> 00:46:28,246
- (Horns honking)
- Dobie!

563
00:46:30,655 --> 00:46:32,555
Dobie!

564
00:47:18,636 --> 00:47:21,070
So what's it gonna be, Paul?

565
00:47:26,877 --> 00:47:28,777
Stapleton?

566
00:47:58,609 --> 00:48:00,474
(Children laugh)

567
00:48:42,553 --> 00:48:44,646
(Growling)

568
00:48:54,298 --> 00:48:56,129
(Growling continues )

569
00:49:24,295 --> 00:49:26,422
She just woke up.

570
00:49:37,141 --> 00:49:40,008
Stand away from the door, please.

571
00:49:40,678 --> 00:49:43,738
I don't know who you are
or where I am,

572
00:49:43,814 --> 00:49:46,476
but I'm being held against my will,

573
00:49:46,584 --> 00:49:48,711
and I want to use the telephone.

574
00:49:48,786 --> 00:49:50,777
I'd like you to sit on the bed.

575
00:49:50,855 --> 00:49:54,882
I've found my husband's dead body,
and I want the phone!

576
00:49:54,959 --> 00:49:57,553
After you've seen Dr Silverman.

577
00:49:57,695 --> 00:50:00,789
- What is this place?
- Stapleton Hospital.

578
00:50:00,865 --> 00:50:03,265
This is Rosco, and I'm Nurse Floyd.

579
00:50:03,334 --> 00:50:06,861
Well, fuck both of you.
I want Silverman in here now!

580
00:50:06,937 --> 00:50:10,031
- And I want a phone!
- You're not listening.

581
00:50:10,174 --> 00:50:12,540
I just explained about the phone.

582
00:50:12,643 --> 00:50:14,543
Why don't you understand?

583
00:50:14,612 --> 00:50:17,274
I was just in the Carlton Hotel,

584
00:50:17,381 --> 00:50:20,839
and in room 401 is the body
of my murdered husband.

585
00:50:20,918 --> 00:50:22,943
Want me to put her on the bed?

586
00:50:23,020 --> 00:50:26,251
- I'm just gonna put you...
- No! I'll kill you!

587
00:50:26,323 --> 00:50:30,350
- Can I call someone for you?
- Call the fucking police.

588
00:50:30,427 --> 00:50:34,864
My husband's being eaten by a dog
in a hotel room in Hammond.

589
00:50:37,902 --> 00:50:40,063
(Laughing)

590
00:50:40,171 --> 00:50:42,332
Why are you laughing, Claire?

591
00:50:45,109 --> 00:50:47,270
Cos...

592
00:50:47,378 --> 00:50:49,608
the bastard's in my head.

593
00:50:50,681 --> 00:50:52,945
He's fucked up my brain.

594
00:50:53,250 --> 00:50:55,684
And now he's murdered my husband.

595
00:50:58,055 --> 00:50:59,784
Oh.

596
00:51:00,057 --> 00:51:02,890
Oh, God!

597
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:06,452
- It's happening again!
- What's happening, Claire?

598
00:51:06,530 --> 00:51:09,829
What? What are they doing?

599
00:51:10,067 --> 00:51:14,060
NO! NO!

600
00:51:14,138 --> 00:51:16,038
(Claire screams )

601
00:51:19,476 --> 00:51:21,569
(Rosco ) We're here to help.

602
00:51:26,584 --> 00:51:28,643
How is she?

603
00:51:29,253 --> 00:51:31,312
Terrible.

604
00:51:31,388 --> 00:51:33,856
I'm gonna sell this house.

605
00:51:35,626 --> 00:51:39,027
I need to get her a new shrink.

606
00:51:39,096 --> 00:51:41,223
Want a second opinion?

607
00:51:41,298 --> 00:51:43,732
Yeah. I want 20 of 'em.

608
00:51:43,801 --> 00:51:47,601
Whatever it takes
to get her out of that place.

609
00:51:47,671 --> 00:51:49,298
(Phone )

610
00:51:55,012 --> 00:51:59,381
There's a lady on the phone.
Says she found Dobie near some hotel.

611
00:52:00,217 --> 00:52:02,242
- Hello?
- 'Mr Cooper?'

612
00:52:11,328 --> 00:52:15,697
(Groggily) Doctor, don't...don't
let Paul go to the hotel.

613
00:52:15,799 --> 00:52:17,824
Don't let him go.

614
00:52:18,836 --> 00:52:22,772
- Is this a real hotel?
- It doesn't matter. The Carlton.

615
00:52:22,907 --> 00:52:25,637
It's by the ocean in Hammond.

616
00:52:25,709 --> 00:52:29,873
- When were you there?
- Last night, room 401.

617
00:52:29,980 --> 00:52:33,416
So it's not real. You dreamt it.

618
00:52:33,517 --> 00:52:37,044
- Was it day or night?
- Daytime. Please call him.

619
00:52:49,033 --> 00:52:51,934
(Silverman )
Does he meet someone there?

620
00:52:52,002 --> 00:52:56,496
- He goes to find Dobie.
- Is Dobie a woman, Claire?

621
00:52:56,674 --> 00:52:58,539
(Groaning)

622
00:53:01,612 --> 00:53:03,637
He's a fucking dog.

623
00:53:17,928 --> 00:53:22,331
What have you given me, Doctor?
Why can't I think straight?

624
00:53:22,399 --> 00:53:26,358
Thorazine. It calms you down.

625
00:53:30,607 --> 00:53:33,701
(Silverman )
'What happens to him there?'

626
00:53:34,311 --> 00:53:36,370
(Claire ) 'He dies.'

627
00:53:36,447 --> 00:53:39,041
(Sobbing) Doctor...

628
00:53:40,184 --> 00:53:44,848
Don't you get it, Doctor?
401. Room 401.

629
00:53:44,955 --> 00:53:47,219
How many times do I have to say it?

630
00:53:47,291 --> 00:53:50,920
(Silverman )
'So you dreamt that Paul died.'

631
00:53:50,995 --> 00:53:54,522
I dreamt it and it happens.

632
00:53:56,066 --> 00:53:58,091
It's going to happen.

633
00:53:58,202 --> 00:54:02,366
Can't you get it through
your thick psytiactric skull?

634
00:54:02,439 --> 00:54:06,535
The man I love is dead and I'm left
in this God-awful place alone!

635
00:54:08,979 --> 00:54:10,378
Hello?

636
00:54:10,481 --> 00:54:13,075
(Silverman )
'You mean dead to you, Claire.'

637
00:54:13,150 --> 00:54:16,119
No, no, I mean dead like Rebecca.

638
00:54:16,186 --> 00:54:18,916
How many ways can I fucking say it?

639
00:54:19,790 --> 00:54:21,655
Do...

640
00:54:23,627 --> 00:54:27,427
- What the fuck?
- (Silverman ) 'It's called grief.'

641
00:54:27,498 --> 00:54:30,365
No, no, it's Paul this time.

642
00:54:31,435 --> 00:54:33,960
Please. God, listen to me.

643
00:54:34,071 --> 00:54:36,596
- (Whimpering)
- What's this?

644
00:54:37,708 --> 00:54:38,936
Listen to me!

645
00:54:39,743 --> 00:54:41,802
Hi, Paul!

646
00:54:42,279 --> 00:54:43,541
Shit!

647
00:54:43,614 --> 00:54:45,445
(Alarm )

648
00:54:49,353 --> 00:54:52,379
Listen to me! Listen to me!

649
00:54:52,456 --> 00:54:56,483
- Listen to me! Oh! No!
- Come on. Get up.

650
00:54:56,660 --> 00:54:58,890
Come on!

651
00:54:59,229 --> 00:55:01,663
(Claire ) Listen!

652
00:55:01,732 --> 00:55:05,600
Listen to me!

653
00:55:05,702 --> 00:55:07,533
Listen!

654
00:55:07,604 --> 00:55:11,904
(Rosco ) OK, we're going
to give you something to relax.

655
00:55:11,975 --> 00:55:14,603
All right, get her down.

656
00:55:14,678 --> 00:55:18,808
- Please, let me go!
- Just relax.

657
00:55:18,882 --> 00:55:22,648
- Please, no.
- We're going to give you something.

658
00:55:32,162 --> 00:55:34,630
Brought you some hot tea, honey.

659
00:55:34,698 --> 00:55:37,030
It'll still be warm.

660
00:55:37,101 --> 00:55:41,697
- I'm sorry. Do I know you?
- You're sharin' a room with me.

661
00:55:41,772 --> 00:55:45,708
- They want me to keep an eye on you.
- I don't remember.

662
00:55:45,843 --> 00:55:49,279
- You got some people in your head.
- Hmm.

663
00:56:28,418 --> 00:56:30,477
(Bang)

664
00:56:45,302 --> 00:56:49,432
What's the matter, honey?
You don't like the pattern?

665
00:56:57,014 --> 00:56:59,448
(Whispers ) Can you keep a secret?

666
00:56:59,516 --> 00:57:01,711
(Whispers ) Probably.

667
00:57:04,054 --> 00:57:06,113
You won't think I'm crazy?

668
00:57:06,223 --> 00:57:08,555
(Chuckling) Probably! I mean...

669
00:57:08,625 --> 00:57:13,426
That man in my head was in
this hospital when he was a boy.

670
00:57:13,497 --> 00:57:15,124
How do you know?

671
00:57:15,199 --> 00:57:19,863
He stayed in this room.
He wrote that.

672
00:57:19,970 --> 00:57:22,165
His name's Vivian Thompson.

673
00:57:22,239 --> 00:57:24,264
Ooh, la-la! (Chuckles )

674
00:57:29,079 --> 00:57:31,513
Did anyone ever get out of here?

675
00:57:31,582 --> 00:57:34,244
I wouldn't start thinkin' that.

676
00:57:34,318 --> 00:57:39,051
I'm not talking about me.
I'm talking about somebody else.

677
00:57:39,122 --> 00:57:41,022
It's not that difficult.

678
00:57:41,091 --> 00:57:44,151
When you've been here
as long as I have

679
00:57:44,261 --> 00:57:47,094
you get to know the language
of the place.

680
00:57:47,831 --> 00:57:49,856
Go to sleep.

681
00:58:07,684 --> 00:58:11,245
(Girl) Hi! What's your name?
(Woman ) Ruby!

682
00:58:11,355 --> 00:58:13,414
Oh, sorry. I gotta go.

683
00:58:14,024 --> 00:58:15,958
Ruby!

684
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:19,462
Come on. I'm runnin' late.

685
00:58:19,563 --> 00:58:22,464
- Mommy's in a hurry.
- You're not my mommy.

686
00:58:22,532 --> 00:58:26,764
(Claire ) 'He's hunting...
looking for another little girl.'

687
00:58:26,870 --> 00:58:31,864
Guess what her name is, Doctor.
Ruby.

688
00:58:31,975 --> 00:58:34,102
And what colour is Ruby, Claire?

689
00:58:34,211 --> 00:58:37,305
Ruby's not a colour, Doctor.
Ruby's a girl.

690
00:58:37,381 --> 00:58:42,250
Red. Why are you obsessed
with that colour, Claire?

691
00:58:42,352 --> 00:58:45,685
I'm not obsessed,
I'm possessed, Doctor.

692
00:58:45,789 --> 00:58:48,690
