693
00:58:49,760 --> 00:58:51,625
Why's that, Claire?

694
00:58:51,762 --> 00:58:56,631
Maybe he's lonely.
Maybe he's lonely, Doctor.

695
00:58:58,135 --> 00:59:00,365
Have you a name for him yet?

696
00:59:00,470 --> 00:59:04,429
Yes, I have.
His name is Vivian. Vivian Thompson.

697
00:59:04,574 --> 00:59:08,533
There's a town covered in water.
Someone left him in it.

698
00:59:08,612 --> 00:59:10,705
He was taken to this hospital.

699
00:59:10,781 --> 00:59:14,717
He stayed in my room
and he's feeding me dreams.

700
00:59:14,785 --> 00:59:17,515
Why do you think that is, Doctor?

701
00:59:17,754 --> 00:59:22,748
Because he wants to stop.
He wants me to stop him.

702
00:59:22,926 --> 00:59:25,360
It sounds psychotic to you,
doesn't it?

703
00:59:25,462 --> 00:59:27,726
You used that word, Claire.

704
00:59:27,898 --> 00:59:31,595
But follow it through,
Doctor, psychotic or not.

705
00:59:31,668 --> 00:59:35,035
I've gotta let him possess me...
surrender...

706
00:59:35,172 --> 00:59:37,732
Let him take me to him.

707
00:59:37,808 --> 00:59:43,075
So what does that make me? Psychotic?
Delusional? Obsessional? All three?

708
00:59:43,180 --> 00:59:47,742
If you admit that it's delusional,
we might be getting someplace.

709
01:00:08,004 --> 01:00:10,734
So, what's it say
on the wall, Ethel?

710
01:00:10,807 --> 01:00:13,970
It's some kind of nursery rhyme.

711
01:00:14,044 --> 01:00:16,706
So, I'm not insane?

712
01:00:17,814 --> 01:00:20,510
Not many of us are, honey.

713
01:00:22,185 --> 01:00:25,518
- Go to sleep.
- That's a good idea.

714
01:00:25,622 --> 01:00:28,056
Sleep's the only way to reach him.

715
01:00:28,125 --> 01:00:31,322
He's out there hunting another
little girl, and I've gotta stop him.

716
01:00:33,663 --> 01:00:38,225
Whatever happens, though, promise me
one thing - don't wake me up.

717
01:01:27,918 --> 01:01:29,783
(Gasps )

718
01:02:03,954 --> 01:02:06,286
(Screaming)

719
01:02:17,467 --> 01:02:19,765
(Screaming continues )

720
01:02:37,220 --> 01:02:39,051
My apologies, Claire.

721
01:05:47,277 --> 01:05:51,111
(Rosco ) That's it, Jodie.
Let the medication do the job.

722
01:05:51,247 --> 01:05:53,943
You just relax and sleep.

723
01:05:54,751 --> 01:05:56,651
You'll be fine.

724
01:06:18,341 --> 01:06:20,241
Oh! Excuse me.

725
01:06:24,948 --> 01:06:26,848
(Crickets chirping)

726
01:06:49,506 --> 01:06:52,441
Hey. You need a lift?

727
01:06:52,575 --> 01:06:54,406
I'm waitin' for Lucy.

728
01:06:54,477 --> 01:06:59,039
- Everything all right?
- No, I...

729
01:06:59,149 --> 01:07:02,118
locked myself out of my car.

730
01:07:02,218 --> 01:07:05,210
Come back to the office.
You can use the phone.

731
01:07:05,321 --> 01:07:10,156
Uh, I have a spare,
uh, set...at a garage.

732
01:07:11,394 --> 01:07:14,625
If you're going out,
you could drop me.

733
01:07:15,365 --> 01:07:18,664
- Which garage?
- The one down the road.

734
01:07:19,702 --> 01:07:22,569
- Got your ID?
- It's locked in the car.

735
01:07:23,840 --> 01:07:25,865
All right. Hop in.

736
01:07:31,648 --> 01:07:36,813
So, uh, do you want to get a drink
