753
01:08:59,435 --> 01:09:01,300
I suppose they should've.

754
01:09:03,740 --> 01:09:05,833
You can kiss me if you want.

755
01:09:06,910 --> 01:09:09,276
Don't mind if I do.

756
01:09:12,015 --> 01:09:13,448
(Giggling)

757
01:09:15,118 --> 01:09:17,313
- What the fuck?
- (Laughs )

758
01:09:18,488 --> 01:09:20,683
Two things, Walter.

759
01:09:20,790 --> 01:09:24,726
- One, get out of the car slowly.
- Mm-hmm.

760
01:09:24,827 --> 01:09:29,628
And two, get your ass back
to Stapleton and tell Silverman

761
01:09:29,699 --> 01:09:32,167
to check out the Carlton Hotel.

762
01:09:46,416 --> 01:09:48,611
Why are we here?

763
01:09:48,685 --> 01:09:50,983
That's my home.

764
01:09:51,087 --> 01:09:53,783
A lake? You live in a lake?

765
01:09:56,125 --> 01:09:58,184
Did once.

766
01:10:06,803 --> 01:10:08,668
(Splash)

767
01:10:31,127 --> 01:10:34,028
(Whispering)
Where did you go, Vivian?

768
01:10:35,665 --> 01:10:38,259
Please, please don't leave me now.

769
01:10:41,504 --> 01:10:44,598
(Footsteps )

770
01:11:02,859 --> 01:11:05,760
Wanna come over to my house, Claire?

771
01:11:06,462 --> 01:11:08,362
Yeah.

772
01:11:08,498 --> 01:11:11,763
I have to warn you, it's haunted.

773
01:11:11,868 --> 01:11:14,268
Who's it haunted by?

774
01:11:14,337 --> 01:11:16,237
You.

775
01:11:36,426 --> 01:11:39,725
I'll show you how to get there.
You can drive now.

776
01:11:47,770 --> 01:11:52,537
Vivian, is there a girl
in your house called Ruby?

777
01:11:52,642 --> 01:11:55,008
Ruby? Yeah.

778
01:11:57,647 --> 01:12:01,845
- She's dying to meet you.
- Oh, God.

779
01:12:01,918 --> 01:12:04,216
You thought it was a real orchard?

780
01:12:04,287 --> 01:12:08,587
That's the thing about dreams,
They're always right...

781
01:12:08,658 --> 01:12:10,717
and always wrong.

782
01:12:16,732 --> 01:12:20,099
You have to drive inside, OK?
I'll open the door.

783
01:12:48,164 --> 01:12:50,689
You know this place,
don't you, Claire?

784
01:12:56,339 --> 01:12:59,433
- Yes.
- You know the funny thing?

785
01:12:59,509 --> 01:13:02,239
What's the funny thing?

786
01:13:02,345 --> 01:13:07,783
I know you got a gun in the band
of the nurse's dress you're wearing.

787
01:13:07,884 --> 01:13:10,114
- I do?
- You do!

788
01:13:10,186 --> 01:13:14,088
And it's not very nice,
you meetin' Ruby with a gun.

789
01:13:14,157 --> 01:13:17,684
Might get her upset.
Might get me upset...

790
01:13:17,793 --> 01:13:20,626
and bring the apples
down on all of us.

791
01:13:21,864 --> 01:13:25,197
- Where is Ruby?
- Ubi est Ruby?

792
01:13:26,669 --> 01:13:29,467
I'm not tellin'
till you gimme the gun.

793
01:13:40,316 --> 01:13:43,376
You know what happens
when the apples fall?

794
01:13:43,452 --> 01:13:45,044
I don't.

795
01:13:52,195 --> 01:13:57,223
# First the tide

796
01:13:58,334 --> 01:14:00,495
# Rushes in

797
01:14:02,638 --> 01:14:06,904
# Plants a kiss

798
01:14:07,043 --> 01:14:10,171
# On the shore

799
01:14:11,113 --> 01:14:15,049
# Then rolls... #

800
01:14:15,151 --> 01:14:19,781
I'm so, so
sorry, sorry, sorry, Claire.

801
01:14:21,424 --> 01:14:23,790
All I wanted was a family.

802
01:14:23,926 --> 01:14:29,193
I knew there was a dreamer out there
like me, cos I was dreamin' of her.

803
01:14:29,332 --> 01:14:31,630
I wanted her to be my family.

804
01:14:33,336 --> 01:14:36,464
And I took her little girl.

805
01:14:36,572 --> 01:14:40,941
And the little girl cried
and hollered,

806
01:14:42,311 --> 01:14:46,179
and I punished her
like any dad would.

807
01:14:48,017 --> 01:14:50,042
- And she was lying...
- (Sobbing)

808
01:14:50,219 --> 01:14:53,154
quiet, beautiful...

809
01:14:54,323 --> 01:14:56,382
but like a doll now.

810
01:14:58,194 --> 01:15:00,788
- That's the part I'm sorry for.
- (Gasping)

811
01:15:00,863 --> 01:15:03,263
But I'm gonna make it up to you.

812
01:15:03,366 --> 01:15:05,391
I'm gonna work...

813
01:15:05,468 --> 01:15:07,527
real hard.

814
01:15:07,770 --> 01:15:09,829
Make it perfect.

815
01:15:10,640 --> 01:15:14,599
I'm not gonna get upset anymore
now that I've got you here,

816
01:15:14,677 --> 01:15:17,145
and I got us Ruby for a daughter now.

817
01:15:19,382 --> 01:15:22,840
Claire and Vivian and Ruby.
(Chuckles )

818
01:15:24,086 --> 01:15:28,386
Did you... Did you get upset
with Ruby, Vivian?

819
01:15:28,457 --> 01:15:30,584
- Not yet. Not yet.
- Did you?

820
01:15:30,693 --> 01:15:32,888
Are you gonna get upset with me?

821
01:15:34,463 --> 01:15:38,229
Not if you love me
like Mama loves Dad. Will you?

822
01:15:39,302 --> 01:15:41,736
I'll do that, Vivian.

823
01:15:44,040 --> 01:15:46,099
I'll do that.

824
01:15:47,243 --> 01:15:50,144
You wouldn't just pretend?

825
01:15:50,279 --> 01:15:52,304
How could I pretend?

826
01:15:54,350 --> 01:15:57,410
How could I pretend with you, Vivian?

827
01:15:57,520 --> 01:16:00,455
You know me inside and out.

828
01:16:00,523 --> 01:16:02,957
Things are gonna be perfect...

829
01:16:04,060 --> 01:16:06,119
when I see Ruby.

830
01:16:07,330 --> 01:16:10,697
As perfect as they can be
in this valley of tears.

831
01:16:22,411 --> 01:16:26,347
- Oh, Lordy.
- What the fuck is this?

832
01:16:26,415 --> 01:16:30,249
Her dream, Rosco. Your nightmare.

833
01:16:33,489 --> 01:16:37,220
(Vivian ) Ruby, guess who's here?
Say hi to Ruby, Claire.

834
01:16:42,798 --> 01:16:45,767
- Hello, Ruby.
- Are you a ghost?

835
01:16:45,901 --> 01:16:47,562
No, I'm not.

836
01:16:47,636 --> 01:16:52,801
She was a ghost when she wasn't here.
Now she's just plain old Claire.

837
01:16:52,875 --> 01:16:58,211
Why don't you go down in the garden
and show Ruby you're not a ghost?

838
01:16:58,280 --> 01:17:01,807
He said you were coming.
You took a long time.

839
01:17:02,618 --> 01:17:06,816
I know. It was gettin' kinda lonesome
here just the two of us, huh?

840
01:17:06,889 --> 01:17:09,949
I suppose. This is Marge.

841
01:17:10,025 --> 01:17:13,620
She was Vivian's doll
before he gave her to me.

842
01:17:13,696 --> 01:17:19,293
Say hello to Claire, Marge.
That nice lady is not a ghost.

843
01:17:19,368 --> 01:17:21,598
Hello, Claire! Welcome home!

844
01:17:22,705 --> 01:17:25,003
Welcome home, Claire.

845
01:17:26,475 --> 01:17:28,909
- She's followed him.
- Who?

846
01:17:28,978 --> 01:17:33,415
Vivian Thompson. He escaped
through that grate. Murdered a nurse.

847
01:17:33,482 --> 01:17:36,417
- When?
- 25 years ago. October 1972.

848
01:17:36,485 --> 01:17:38,976
- I'm lost, Doctor.
- Join the club.

849
01:17:40,122 --> 01:17:42,181
He killed her daughter.

850
01:17:43,058 --> 01:17:47,825
She shares his dreams. He snatched
another little girl called Ruby.

851
01:17:51,400 --> 01:17:55,461
She's gone to stop him.
Call the police. Show them this.

852
01:17:55,604 --> 01:17:59,438
- Where are you going?
- Hammond, the Carlton Hotel.

853
01:18:00,309 --> 01:18:03,073
I'll make us somethin' to eat.
Is anyone hungry?

854
01:18:03,179 --> 01:18:05,079
How about "pasghetti"?

855
01:18:08,584 --> 01:18:12,042
Daddies can be just like mommies,
you know that?

856
01:18:12,121 --> 01:18:16,717
- Can they, honey?
- Vivian said so. They can cook too.

857
01:18:20,763 --> 01:18:23,095
What else did he tell you, Ruby?

858
01:18:23,165 --> 01:18:26,726
Told me my real mom
is up in Heaven waiting for me.

859
01:18:28,270 --> 01:18:30,204
That's Vivian's mom there.

860
01:18:30,272 --> 01:18:32,797
(Claire )
That's a tailor's dummy, Ruby.

861
01:18:32,908 --> 01:18:36,105
I know, but that's
the kind of clothes she wore.

862
01:18:36,178 --> 01:18:39,170
- Why does he keep them?
- For playing mom.

863
01:18:39,281 --> 01:18:44,150
He's very good at it. You should
hear the way his voice changes.

864
01:18:44,220 --> 01:18:46,313
Why does he do that?

865
01:18:46,388 --> 01:18:50,222
He says his daddy was a dollar
and his mommy was a song.

866
01:18:50,292 --> 01:18:51,623
A song?

867
01:18:51,694 --> 01:18:55,824
"Don't Sit Under The Apple Tree
With Anyone Else But Me."

868
01:18:55,965 --> 01:18:58,525
So that's his mother's song.

869
01:18:58,601 --> 01:19:01,069
That's what she was, that song.

870
01:19:14,550 --> 01:19:16,609
I don't like the cold.

871
01:19:18,621 --> 01:19:20,748
Ruby...

872
01:19:20,890 --> 01:19:23,154
Ruby, listen to me, OK?

873
01:19:23,225 --> 01:19:26,251
Vivian's sick, honey,
and he needs help.

874
01:19:26,328 --> 01:19:30,697
- It's possible he could hurt you.
- You're scaring me.

875
01:19:30,799 --> 01:19:34,291
- I'm gonna take you away from here.
- Vivian!

876
01:19:34,436 --> 01:19:37,030
Shh! Quiet!

877
01:19:37,106 --> 01:19:41,770
I've been looking for the can opener,
but I can't...find it!

878
01:19:43,946 --> 01:19:45,971
I know it's down there.

879
01:19:48,050 --> 01:19:51,417
Sometimes Mommy and Daddy fight
and that's bad.

880
01:19:51,487 --> 01:19:54,388
Sometimes they fight and that's good.

881
01:19:57,126 --> 01:19:59,686
She's so, so, so tired.

882
01:20:01,030 --> 01:20:03,055
You help me find it?

883
01:20:03,132 --> 01:20:07,865
Cos you're the girl. And when we
find it you can have some...snacks.

884
01:20:07,937 --> 01:20:10,997
And then when she wakes up
we'll feed her too.

885
01:20:12,474 --> 01:20:14,635
You gonna say you're sorry now?

886
01:20:14,710 --> 01:20:18,305
# Don't sit under the apple tree
with anyone else but me

887
01:20:18,380 --> 01:20:19,870
# Anyone else but me... #

888
01:20:19,949 --> 01:20:24,079
Cat got your tongue?
You're worse than your goddam daddy!

889
01:20:24,186 --> 01:20:27,815
# Don't sit under the apple tree
with anyone else but me

890
01:20:27,890 --> 01:20:31,758
# Till I come marching home... #

891
01:20:32,861 --> 01:20:35,352
(Song continues, muffled)

892
01:20:39,501 --> 01:20:41,401
(Whimpers )

893
01:20:47,076 --> 01:20:50,341
(Ruby ) You got him real mad.

894
01:20:51,680 --> 01:20:55,241
That's why he put you
in bad mommy's clothes.

895
01:20:55,351 --> 01:20:57,842
He says he's disappointed in you.

896
01:20:57,920 --> 01:21:03,017
He told me you'd be the loveliest
mommy in the whole wide world.

897
01:21:06,528 --> 01:21:08,587
Does your face hurt?

898
01:21:09,732 --> 01:21:11,825
I can kiss it better.

899
01:21:13,068 --> 01:21:16,094
Is that better?
Are you tied too tight?

900
01:21:16,205 --> 01:21:19,038
I'd loosen it,
but he might get mad again.

901
01:21:19,141 --> 01:21:22,440
- I'd never seen him mad before.
- (Vivian ) Ruby!

902
01:21:37,693 --> 01:21:40,059
- Dr Silverman?
- Yeah.

903
01:21:40,162 --> 01:21:42,460
You know this place?

904
01:21:42,531 --> 01:21:44,624
I was told about it.

905
01:21:44,700 --> 01:21:46,793
Let's get some light in there.

906
01:21:47,202 --> 01:21:49,227
Sweet Jesus!

907
01:21:52,675 --> 01:21:56,907
(Vivian ) # ..with anyone else but me

908
01:21:56,979 --> 01:21:59,447
# Anyone else but me

909
01:21:59,581 --> 01:22:01,606
# With anyone else but me #

910
01:22:03,652 --> 01:22:05,677
Bedtime, Ruby. Undo me, OK?

911
01:22:06,722 --> 01:22:10,624
Time to move over, Claire.
Thank you, sweetums.

912
01:22:10,693 --> 01:22:12,752
Go snuggle up with Mommy.

913
01:22:15,297 --> 01:22:17,993
I'd never hurt you, Claire.

914
01:22:24,139 --> 01:22:28,235
(Chuckles ) Didn't mind
hurting Paul, though, did I?

915
01:22:29,745 --> 01:22:32,179
I thought you'd be a better mommy.

916
01:22:32,247 --> 01:22:34,875
My mom was no good either.

917
01:22:35,084 --> 01:22:36,779
She...

918
01:22:38,220 --> 01:22:40,552
wore dresses like that.

919
01:22:45,227 --> 01:22:47,491
# Never knew my dad

920
01:22:47,596 --> 01:22:49,621
# Mom was all I had #

921
01:22:49,865 --> 01:22:51,162
NO!

922
01:22:55,404 --> 01:22:57,201
Please?

923
01:22:58,574 --> 01:23:00,735
Got eyes in the back of my head.

924
01:23:00,809 --> 01:23:05,906
When Mom said
it was time for bed, I...

925
01:23:06,014 --> 01:23:07,914
I believed her.

926
01:23:08,016 --> 01:23:10,780
Sorry if I'm moody.
It's been a long day.

927
01:23:10,886 --> 01:23:13,184
Things didn't turn out the way...

928
01:23:14,690 --> 01:23:16,749
I thought they would.

929
01:23:20,262 --> 01:23:24,198
Now I'm gonna kiss you...

930
01:23:24,299 --> 01:23:26,927
- good night.
- Ah!

931
01:23:27,069 --> 01:23:30,163
- Ow.
- Take a cheek, Ruby.

932
01:24:04,640 --> 01:24:06,938
(Gasping)

933
01:24:08,177 --> 01:24:10,077
- Oh, God.
- Shh.

934
01:24:10,212 --> 01:24:12,077
- Claire?
- Shh, shh, shh, shh. Yes?

935
01:24:12,181 --> 01:24:14,046
- Claire?
- Yes?

936
01:24:14,216 --> 01:24:16,241
I just had a bad dream.

937
01:24:18,387 --> 01:24:21,447
I dreamt my mommy
was dead in the lake...

938
01:24:22,724 --> 01:24:25,056
and she had your face.

939
01:24:25,127 --> 01:24:27,152
(Sobs )

940
01:24:28,197 --> 01:24:31,064
Does that mean you're gonna kill me?

941
01:24:34,403 --> 01:24:36,462
I hope not.

942
01:24:47,416 --> 01:24:51,512
- Any word on the car she took?
- It was seen on Route Nine.

943
01:24:51,587 --> 01:24:53,851
- Great, let's go.
- All right.

944
01:25:00,562 --> 01:25:02,860
You're not such a bad mom.

945
01:25:06,635 --> 01:25:08,762
Don't get him mad again.

946
01:25:21,016 --> 01:25:22,074
(Screams )

947
01:25:22,150 --> 01:25:24,482
I don't like you any more.

948
01:25:24,553 --> 01:25:27,716
- I die in the lake, remember?
- I forgot that.

949
01:25:27,789 --> 01:25:30,952
- Maybe you develop a limp.
- I emptied it.

950
01:25:32,361 --> 01:25:34,295
(Claire ) Run!

951
01:25:35,864 --> 01:25:37,729
Run, Ruby!

952
01:25:39,768 --> 01:25:43,204
Run! Wait! Stop.

953
01:25:43,272 --> 01:25:45,934
Come here. Now, you gotta
be brave now, Ruby.

954
01:25:46,074 --> 01:25:49,532
- You gotta be brave, honey.
- Yes. You gotta come with me.

955
01:25:49,678 --> 01:25:52,408
- It's me he wants, not you.
- Claire!

956
01:25:55,951 --> 01:25:58,010
Vivian.

957
01:26:00,522 --> 01:26:02,251
Mom?

958
01:26:03,258 --> 01:26:06,159
You gonna say you're sorry now?

959
01:26:06,795 --> 01:26:09,161
I...don't...WANNA!

960
01:26:12,935 --> 01:26:14,994
(Sirens wailing)

961
01:26:16,138 --> 01:26:19,835
Route Nine. Just made visual
contact with ground units.

962
01:26:20,642 --> 01:26:22,769
(Vivian, wailing) Mom!

963
01:26:25,113 --> 01:26:27,172
Something's wrong.

964
01:26:32,621 --> 01:26:34,452
Mom?

965
01:26:36,358 --> 01:26:39,555
(Whispers ) The cat got my tongue.

966
01:26:42,998 --> 01:26:47,094
Mom? It hurts real bad.

967
01:26:47,169 --> 01:26:51,196
Ruby, where the fuck are you?!

968
01:26:57,980 --> 01:26:59,845
(Vivian ) Claire!

969
01:27:13,295 --> 01:27:15,320
It still hurts!

970
01:27:16,798 --> 01:27:18,891
Gonna kiss and make it better!

971
01:27:20,602 --> 01:27:24,231
Every couple has their problems.
We have to talk!

972
01:27:28,577 --> 01:27:30,442
Two-six to dispatch.

973
01:27:30,512 --> 01:27:35,347
I have a young girl fitting
the description of the subject.

974
01:27:36,318 --> 01:27:38,286
Don't you want to work it out?

975
01:27:38,387 --> 01:27:41,117
Or is it just too late
for me and you?

976
01:27:41,189 --> 01:27:44,681
I know how it goes now -
Ruby makes it to the road.

977
01:27:44,760 --> 01:27:47,490
She stops a car, maybe a police car.

978
01:27:47,596 --> 01:27:51,965
The policeman comes in
and there's all this hostage stuff!

979
01:27:52,034 --> 01:27:54,662
- Is that how it goes?
- Uh-huh.

980
01:27:54,736 --> 01:27:57,136
Maybe Claire breaks her neck!

981
01:27:57,205 --> 01:28:00,538
Oh, I don't want this to happen(!)

982
01:28:00,609 --> 01:28:03,942
I really went out of my way
to bring you here!

983
01:28:04,012 --> 01:28:06,139
- Maybe Claire jumps!
- No, please!

984
01:28:10,585 --> 01:28:12,644
Claire!

985
01:28:13,522 --> 01:28:15,422
(Screams ) Claire!

986
01:28:33,875 --> 01:28:38,073
We got a lead. A girl found off
the interstate named Ruby.

987
01:28:38,146 --> 01:28:43,083
Head due east, we're looking
for a large wooden structure.

988
01:28:43,151 --> 01:28:45,779
- A cider factory.
- Roger that.

989
01:28:50,559 --> 01:28:52,686
Claire!

990
01:28:54,029 --> 01:28:55,963
Claire!

991
01:28:56,798 --> 01:28:58,891
Where are you?

992
01:29:16,084 --> 01:29:18,382
(Vivian screams )

993
01:29:59,861 --> 01:30:03,763
This is Air Seven.
Have established visual contact.

994
01:30:04,900 --> 01:30:08,427
Hey! Hey! Hey!

995
01:30:11,740 --> 01:30:13,708
He's back there!

996
01:30:13,975 --> 01:30:15,408
Back there!

997
01:30:18,613 --> 01:30:22,242
Now there's all this hostage stuff.
I told you so!

998
01:30:24,519 --> 01:30:28,046
- You've gotta give yourself up!
- But how?

999
01:30:28,156 --> 01:30:31,284
I let you go,
they'll make a real mess of me.

1000
01:30:35,664 --> 01:30:39,794
- It's empty! There's no bullets!
- Go away! Go away!

1001
01:30:41,002 --> 01:30:42,367
Shoot!

1002
01:31:26,348 --> 01:31:28,873
(Rebecca ) Mirror, mirror on the wall,

1003
01:31:28,950 --> 01:31:32,317
who's the fairest one of all?

1004
01:31:32,387 --> 01:31:35,220
You are.

1005
01:31:35,290 --> 01:31:38,191
Wrong. You are.

